  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1  \u0bae\u0bc1\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf -  \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "One-sided attempt to turn people's protest into a riot - Vasudeva Nanayakkara",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "The people of the country are outraged by the appointment of Ranil Wickremesinghe as the acting president following the departure of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa. Commenting on the theory of democracy, the president should respect the aspirations of the people and step down.",
        "One party is trying to turn the people's protest into a riot, and the people participating in the protest should act with caution, said Vasudeva Nanayakkara, the leader of the Left Democratic Front in the Parliament.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa is facing a crisis that no leader in Sri Lankan political history has ever faced.",
        "This situation would not have arisen for President Gotadabhaya Rajapaksa if he had taken appropriate action at the beginning regarding the wrong economic policy of former Finance Minister Bashil Rajapaksa.",
        "Because the former Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa and President Gotabaya Rajapaksa did not take any action against Bashil Rajapaksa out of fraternal affection, the political future of the Rajapaksas has been completely destroyed and the future of the people of the country has also been affected.",
        "The main victory of the people's struggle is that the president has left the country following the people's fierce struggle.",
        "Following the appointment of Ranil Wickremesinghe as the acting president, the people have become angry and have been involved in protests.",
        "One party is trying to turn the people's protest into violence. The People's Liberation Front should be held responsible for the protest in the parliamentary constituency.",
        "As the responsible party when the country is in a state of unrest, they should cooperate to solve the crisis through the constitution rather than inciting the people.",
        "Commenting on the principle of democracy, President Ranil Wickremesinghe said that he should respect the aspirations of the people and step down from office and cooperate to advance the resolutions through the Parliament."
      ],
